as 
<taxonomicName id="096F47C9B200D5F0E2A2C8754D3C0723" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Dissanthelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sclerochloides">
<emphasis id="92C00168BAC24B45196AB20E1C414D53" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Dissanthelium sclerochloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="FFB2C31FF16E73CD100A46F2FB937D71" author="Beetle, AA" journalOrPublisher="Naturaliste Canadien" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="173 - 180" refId="B6" refString="Beetle, AA, 1987. Las Gramineas de Mexico, Tomo II: 1-344. Secretaria de Agricultura y Recursos Hidraulicos: COTECOCA, Mexico.Boivin B, Loeve, D (1960) Poa agassizensis, a new prairie bluegrass. Naturaliste Canadien 87: 173 - 180" title="Las Gramineas de Mexico, Tomo II: 1 - 344. Secretaria de Agricultura y Recursos Hidraulicos: COTECOCA, Mexico. Boivin B, Loeve, D (1960) Poa agassizensis, a new prairie bluegrass." volume="87" year="1987">Beetle (1987)</bibRefCitation>
accepted 
<taxonomicName id="7082C4DAC3707346237F1ACD3E4E7BF8" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Dissanthelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mathewsii">
<emphasis id="3FAAF10FBFC2E5FA7A0754F0C6E0E01C" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Dissanthelium mathewsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ball as the correct name. 
<bibRefCitation id="CAD0ECC588DA3894CF811D367BE0C9F7" author="Soreng, RJ" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" publicationUrl="10.2307/3391995" refId="B46" refString="Soreng, RJ, 1998. An infrageneric classification for Poa in North America, and other notes on sections, species, and subspecies of Poa, Puccinellia, and Dissanthelium (Poaceae). Novon 8: 187-202. ., 10.2307/3391995" title="An infrageneric classification for Poa in North America, and other notes on sections, species, and subspecies of Poa, Puccinellia, and Dissanthelium (Poaceae). Novon 8: 187 - 202." url="10.2307/3391995" year="1998">Soreng (1998)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="8A06F8D61FFB88731CCCC0DA5ECC8D43" author="Refulio-Rodriguez, NF" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="122 - 133" publicationUrl="10.1600/036364412X616701" refId="B41" refString="Refulio-Rodriguez, NF, Columbus, JT, Gillespie, LJ, Peterson, PM, Soreng, RJ, 2012. Molecular phylogeny of Dissanthelium (Poaceae: Pooideae) and its taxonomic implications. Systematic Botany 37: 122 - 133, 10.1600/036364412X616701" title="Molecular phylogeny of Dissanthelium (Poaceae: Pooideae) and its taxonomic implications." url="10.1600/036364412X616701" volume="37" year="2012">
<normalizedToken id="ECED932659CBB8C9473F788DFFD10461" originalValue="Refulio-RodrÃ­guez">Refulio-Rodriguez</normalizedToken>
et al. (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
concluded there were too many intermediates between this and the smaller and shorter spikeleted 
<taxonomicName id="B9180DFAF901BE6FADB26E04C6EB79FB" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Dissanthelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calycina">
<emphasis id="C8A343C0036870C2BE05D9EB751A6ACA" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Dissanthelium calycina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(J. Presl) Kunth, and therefore, treated the taxon as a subspecies or variety. 
<taxonomicName id="94F9BA8304BB1ED236ED23C9A62FC907" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calycina">
<emphasis id="B98C7251A2CC00C84D4A3A69DFF4CB9C" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Poa calycina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis id="605121A45A610A9E29916FF0C6C99B38" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">calycina</emphasis>
and var. 
<emphasis id="C6A1415E35D9FFAEDFBE8D06C4BD7E79" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">mathewsii</emphasis>
are known from Bolivia and Peru. Historically, the species was treated within 
<taxonomicName id="BE274736DB550A63D7B0F1C0543ECCA9" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Dissanthelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="43553E55075D82B4D1273558FEBC048D" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Dissanthelium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, DNA analyses have confirmed that all elements of that genus belong within 
<taxonomicName id="BF234C3F98E5D842DBA3E6DAFFA8644C" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3857213E52D6D20D70B3582C6BEA25AB" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Poa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A3BABF735CE874B2A7420840FD087448" author="Refulio-Rodriguez, NF" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="122 - 133" publicationUrl="10.1600/036364412X616701" refId="B41" refString="Refulio-Rodriguez, NF, Columbus, JT, Gillespie, LJ, Peterson, PM, Soreng, RJ, 2012. Molecular phylogeny of Dissanthelium (Poaceae: Pooideae) and its taxonomic implications. Systematic Botany 37: 122 - 133, 10.1600/036364412X616701" title="Molecular phylogeny of Dissanthelium (Poaceae: Pooideae) and its taxonomic implications." url="10.1600/036364412X616701" volume="37" year="2012">
<normalizedToken id="7C6ADDE85876851495976216A2009800" originalValue="Refulio-RodrÃ­guez">Refulio-Rodriguez</normalizedToken>
et al. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
). All but one species formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName id="544E1673C2035170AB1A72B7FF5B9CE8" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Dissanthelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0D115FA5A91B420657219EC5BAE650B0" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Dissanthelium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from other 
<taxonomicName id="249C4992CB59C7EF88546D80AC1AA989" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="40C2E1C01A1DBF20BAF00023136C8D05" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Poa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having spikelets with two florets, lemmas 3-nerved (rare in 
<taxonomicName id="CAB92590DB76B2237230384110357CF0" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0FC969F2F60D71D9E1ECE75502A4BFB6" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Poa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and glumes that are longer than at least the lowest lemma (a feature that occurs infrequently in other groups of 
<taxonomicName id="7F9CFF6867F4D601603997C0AF7EEF82" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0EEF25398807BD479D20380D834AC8E4" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Poa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="66F623561159849C7027D0B684351AB7" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calycina">
<emphasis id="38AB427B2ED68214C02BA3C76AA310E3" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Poa calycina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="E0924905AA146383C583471D3BF8A018" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="409B41806E385F1C46E14A3746A2C3D8" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Poa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="2C31C2043DA99D81E013C6EDD31BF8DF" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Dissanthelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FD0939A22FD692DE6D3898B841E46766" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Dissanthelium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Trin.) Refulio (see also 
<taxonomicName id="08F9575B68EEF7ABA209BB51EF5D1B1B" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thomasii">
<emphasis id="6F686D3364D65AC2D26E0D9A4E9B7771" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Poa thomasii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below)
